'''大幹道'''（印地語：ग्रैंड ट्रंक रोड；英語：Grand Trunk Road）連接了[[中亚|中亞地區]]和[[印度次大陸|印度次大陸]]，是亞洲最古老的主要幹道之一<ref>UNESCO, [https://en.unesco.org/silkroad/knowledge-bank/caravanserais-along-grand-trunk-road-pakistan Caravanserais along the Grand Trunk Road in Pakistan] {{Wayback|url=https://en.unesco.org/silkroad/knowledge-bank/caravanserais-along-grand-trunk-road-pakistan |date=20190531124427 }}</ref>。它全長3670千米<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.globalsecurity.org/military/world/india/grand-trunk-road.htm |title=GlobalSecurity.org: Grand Trunk Road |accessdate=2020-09-02 |archive-date=2019-12-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191210155009/https://www.globalsecurity.org/military/world/india/grand-trunk-road.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>，從[[孟加拉国|孟加拉國]]的[[科克斯巴扎爾|科克斯巴扎爾]]到[[阿富汗|阿富汗]]的[[喀布尔|喀布爾]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.dhakatribune.com/heritage/2014/dec/31/road-empires|title=A road to empires|last=Steel|first=Tim|date=1 January 2015|newspaper=[[Dhaka_Tribune|Dhaka Tribune]]|access-date=2016-07-19|archive-date=2016-02-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160211201821/http://www.dhakatribune.com/heritage/2014/dec/31/road-empires|dead-url=yes}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/kolkata/Cuisine-along-G-T-Road/articleshow/48969618.cms|title=Cuisine along G T Road|last=Jhimli Mukherjee Pandey|first=|date=15 September 2015|newspaper=[[The_Times_of_India|The Times of India]]|location=Calcutta|access-date=2016-07-19|archive-date=2017-01-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170105084522/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/kolkata/Cuisine-along-G-T-Road/articleshow/48969618.cms|dead-url=no}}</ref>，經過了[[吉大港市|吉大港]]、[[达卡|達卡]]、[[加尔各答|加爾各答]]、[[德里|德里]]和[[拉合爾|拉合爾]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/roomfordebate/2014/07/03/where-do-borders-need-to-be-redrawn/permeable-lines-on-the-grand-trunk-road|title=How to Redraw the World Map|last=Khanna|first=Parag|date=|work=|newspaper=The New York Times|issn=0362-4331|access-date=2016-07-19|archive-date=2016-08-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160819103029/http://www.nytimes.com/roomfordebate/2014/07/03/where-do-borders-need-to-be-redrawn/permeable-lines-on-the-grand-trunk-road|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="UNESCO">{{Cite web|url=https://whc.unesco.org/en/tentativelists/6056/|title=Sites along the Uttarapath, Badshahi Sadak, Sadak-e-Azam, Grand Trunk Road|last=Centre|first=UNESCO World Heritage|website=UNESCO World Heritage Centre|language=en|access-date=2018-12-26|archive-date=2018-12-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181226184222/https://whc.unesco.org/en/tentativelists/6056/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。孔雀王朝的[[旃陀罗笈多_(孔雀王朝)|旃陀羅笈多]]於前3世紀修築了縱貫古代[[北印度|北印度]]（Uttarapatha）的高速公路<ref name="Vadime">Vadime Elisseeff, p. 159-162, [https://books.google.com/books?id=zRPbecWnkoIC&pg=PA161&dq=sher+shah+suri+maurya+rohtas&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwi0v6muqcPiAhUNX30KHdI5Ae8Q6AEIOTAD#v=onepage&q=sher%20shah%20suri%20maurya%20rohtas&f=false The Silk Roads: Highways of Culture and Commerce] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=zRPbecWnkoIC&pg=PA161&dq=sher+shah+suri+maurya+rohtas&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwi0v6muqcPiAhUNX30KHdI5Ae8Q6AEIOTAD#v=onepage&q=sher%20shah%20suri%20maurya%20rohtas&f=false |date=20200716131400 }}</ref><ref>Farooqui Salma Ahmed, p. 234, [https://books.google.com/books?id=sxhAtCflwOMC&pg=PA234&dq=sher+shah+highway+peshawar+sonargaon&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjlrczu4cXiAhXXfysKHRqLCncQ6AEIPTAE#v=onepage&q=sher%20shah%20highway%20peshawar%20sonargaon&f=false A Comprehensive History of Medieval India: From Twelfth to the Mid-Eighteenth Century] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=sxhAtCflwOMC&pg=PA234&dq=sher+shah+highway+peshawar+sonargaon&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjlrczu4cXiAhXXfysKHRqLCncQ6AEIPTAE#v=onepage&q=sher%20shah%20highway%20peshawar%20sonargaon&f=false |date=20200727090724 }}</ref>，其後繼者[[阿育王|阿育王]]也對該道路進行了修築。這條道路在英國殖民的1833至1860年被大規模翻修<ref>[[David_Arnold_(historian)|David Arnold (historian)]];
Science, technology, and medicine in colonial India (New Cambr hist India v.III.5)
Cambridge University Press, 2000, 234 pages [https://books.google.com/books?id=3gk5j2u5AnUC&pg=PA106 p. 106] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=3gk5j2u5AnUC&pg=PA106 |date=20200114100220 }}</ref>。

幾個世紀以來，這條公路一直是該地區的主要貿易路線之一，為旅行和郵政通訊提供了便利。大主幹道仍在當今的印度次大陸上用於運輸，該地區的部分道路已經拓寬並納入了國家高速公路系統<ref name="raghubir">{{cite book |last1=Singh |first1=Raghubir |year=1995 |title=The Grand Trunk Road: A Passage Through India |url=https://archive.org/details/grandtrunkroadpa00sing |url-access=registration |publisher=Aperture Books |edition=First}}</ref>。

